From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Remove navigator.webdriver automation binding

Detection vector: Browser automation frameworks (Selenium, Playwright,
Puppeteer) set navigator.webdriver = true via the CDP
Page.addScriptToEvaluateOnNewDocument or the --enable-automation Chrome
flag. Detection sites read navigator.webdriver directly, check the
property descriptor shape (configurable + enumerable + has getter), or
probe the V8 binding layer for the automation-specific getter.

This patch makes Navigator::webdriver() always return false regardless
of the browser's automation state. The property descriptor shape is
preserved so it matches a non-automated Chrome instance.

Surface: v8-binding
Closes: webdriverPresent, WEBDRIVER, fpscanner WEBDRIVER

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ bool Navigator::webdriver() const {
-  if (!GetFrame())
-    return false;
-  return GetFrame()->GetDocument()->IsWebDriver();
+  // AgenticBrowser: always report false regardless of automation state.
+  // Detection sites probe navigator.webdriver directly and via descriptor
+  // shape. Returning false with the standard IDL getter matches real Chrome
+  // in non-automated mode.
+  return false;
 }

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.idl
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.idl
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@
-  [HighEntropy, MeasureAs=NavigatorWebDriver] readonly attribute boolean webdriver;
+  // AgenticBrowser: lower entropy — webdriver is always false.
+  [MeasureAs=NavigatorWebDriver] readonly attribute boolean webdriver;

--- a/chrome/test/chromedriver/session.cc
+++ b/chrome/test/chromedriver/session.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@
-  // Inject cdc_ variables for ChromeDriver protocol detection.
+  // AgenticBrowser: skip cdc_ injection to avoid CDP detection signals.
+  // Original: Inject cdc_ variables for ChromeDriver protocol detection.
